<p itemprop="description">A senior security architect leads complex security transformation initiatives and provides strategic direction on security architecture. They influence organisation-wide security decisions and serve as a senior subject matter expert on security technologies, risk management, and compliance.</p>

<section class="role-details">
    <h2>Typical responsibilities</h2>
    <ul>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead enterprise-wide security transformation programmes and strategic initiatives</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Define organisation security strategy and target security architecture</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Establish security architecture governance frameworks and standards</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead complex stakeholder engagement across multiple business areas for security solutions</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Provide expert consultation on strategic security technology decisions</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Mentor and develop security architecture capability across the organisation</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Drive innovation and evaluation of emerging security technologies</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Lead organisation-wide security risk management and compliance initiatives</li>
        <li itemprop="responsibility">Collaborate with enterprise architects on cross-cutting security concerns</li>
    </ul>
</section>

